import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.bar(data['state'], data['rate'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Obesity Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.title('What is the average obesity rate across all states?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    us_states = gpd.read_file('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json')
    us_states = us_states.merge(data, left_on='id', right_on='id')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,10))
    us_states.plot(column='rate', cmap='OrRd', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8')
    ax.axis('off')
    ax.set_title('Which state has the highest obesity rate?', fontdict={'fontsize': '25', 'fontweight' : '3'})
    ax.annotate('Highest rate', xy=(0.5, 0.5), xytext=(0.5, 0.5), fontsize=15, color='white', ha='center', va='center', xycoords='axes fraction', textcoords='axes fraction', bbox=dict(boxstyle='round', facecolor='black', alpha=0.8))
    max_rate = data['rate'].max()
    ax.axhline(y=max_rate, color='black', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest rate: {max_rate:.2%}')
    ax.legend(loc='lower left', frameon=False, fontsize=12)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=10, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['rate'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of obesity rates across all states?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['id'], data['rate'], s=data['rate']*10000, alpha=0.5, c=data['rate'], cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.xlabel('State Population')
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between obesity rate and state population?')
    plt.colorbar(label='Obesity Rate')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['region'] = data['state'].apply(lambda x: x[0])
    sns.boxplot(x='region', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the obesity rate vary across different regions of the US?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
